Package src.controller

Class PatientManager

Object
PatientManager
public class PatientManager extends Object
PatientManager is a controller class responsible for managing patient data, including creating new patient records and updating existing patient details. It provides functionality to create patients, update patient attributes, and view patient records.
Since:
2024-11-20
Version:
1.0
Author:
Benjamin, Kee

  • Method Details

    • createPatient

      public static void createPatient(String name, String dob, Gender gender, String phoneNumber, String email, BloodType bloodType)
      Creates a new patient and adds it to the database.
      Parameters:
      name - The name of the patient.
      dob - The date of birth of the patient.
      gender - The gender of the patient.
      phoneNumber - The phone number of the patient.
      email - The email address of the patient.
      bloodType - The blood type of the patient.

    • updatePatientDetails

      public static boolean updatePatientDetails(String patientID, int attributeCode, String newvalue)
      Updates the details of an existing patient.
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose details are to be updated.
      attributeCode - The attribute to be updated (1 for phone number, 2 for email, 3 for doctor ID, 4 for name).
      newvalue - The new value for the attribute to be updated.
      Returns:
      true if the update was successful, false if the patient was not found.

    • updatePatientDetails

      public static boolean updatePatientDetails(String patientID, int attributeCode, Gender gender)
      Updates the gender of an existing patient.
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose gender is to be updated.
      attributeCode - The attribute code (5 for gender).
      gender - The new gender to be assigned to the patient.
      Returns:
      true if the update was successful, false if the patient was not found.

    • updatePatientDetails

      public static boolean updatePatientDetails(String patientID, int attributeCode, BloodType bloodType)
      Updates the blood type of an existing patient.
      Parameters:
      patientID - The ID of the patient whose blood type is to be updated.
      attributeCode - The attribute code (6 for blood type).
      bloodType - The new blood type to be assigned to the patient.
      Returns:
      true if the update was successful, false if the patient was not found.

    • printAllPatients

      public static void printAllPatients(boolean byID)
      Prints details of all patients in the database, sorted by either Patient ID or Name.
      Parameters:
      byID - if true, sort by Patient ID; if false, sort by Name.

    • showPatientOverview

      public static void showPatientOverview(boolean byID, String doctorId)
      Displays an overview of patients under a specific doctor, sorted by either Patient ID or Name.
      Parameters:
      byID - if true, sort by Patient ID; if false, sort by Name.
      doctorId - the ID of the doctor to filter patients by.

    • validatePatientID

      public static boolean validatePatientID(String patientID)
      Validates if a given patient ID exists in the database.
      Parameters:
      patientID - the ID of the patient to validate.
      Returns:
      true if the patient ID exists; false otherwise.

    • searchPatientByID

      public static Patient searchPatientByID(String patientID)
      Searches for a patient by their ID in the database.
      Parameters:
      patientID - the ID of the patient to search for.
      Returns:
      the Patient object if found; null otherwise.

    • printPastOutcomeRecord

      public static void printPastOutcomeRecord()
